## 10. Update NavMenu

Edit the NavMenu in `ShipmentTracker.Client/Layout/NavMenu.razor` to replace the Counter and Weather links with:
```razor
<div class="nav-item px-3">
    <NavLink class="nav-link" href="dashboard">
        <span class="bi bi-list-nested" aria-hidden="true"></span> Dashboard
    </NavLink>
</div>
<div class="nav-item px-3">
    <NavLink class="nav-link" href="track">
        <span class="bi bi-search" aria-hidden="true"></span> Track Shipment
    </NavLink>
</div>
```

Remove any Counter or Weather nav links.

## 11. Delete template pages

Delete these files if they exist:
- `ShipmentTracker.Client/Pages/Counter.razor`
- `ShipmentTracker.Client/Pages/Weather.razor`
- `ShipmentTracker/Components/Pages/Weather.razor` (if exists)

## 12. Add EF migration

Run: `cd /tmp/sv-0a0d057e53e44b349e26c8a7a153a927/ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker && dotnet ef migrations add AddShipments --output-dir Data/Migrations`

If `dotnet-ef` is not installed, install it first: `dotnet tool install --global dotnet-ef`

Then apply the migration: `dotnet ef database update`

## 13. Build and verify

Run `dotnet build` from the solution directory to verify everything compiles.

IMPORTANT: Make sure to check for existing `_Imports.razor` in the Client project and add necessary using statements for `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization` and `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Authorization` if not already there.
